##A home away from home: "Beipiao" created by new pneumonia

They made requests to the tenants, "self-isolation outside 14 days" , "14 days after the production of three a hospital issued a health certificate.

Reporter

"Don't go back to Beijing yet. "

At around 8 pm on January 30, our reporter arrived at Dongsanqi village, which is located in the north of Beijing. It belongs to seven towns in Changping district. Less than two kilometers south is "Tiantongyuan" community. Beijing is famous for its concentration of migrant workers, both of which house nearly 700,000 permanent residents.

Huinan road will Dongsanqi village into two geographically relatively independent areas, road on both sides of a total of four main doors, in addition to the side doors and small doors, because of the new pneumonia epidemic, all were temporarily locked, only the main door for residents to enter.

Dongsanqi Village Committee Gate (photo by Barge Jing)

One of the main entrance, there are seven or eight staff wearing red armbands and masks, each has its own division of work, the booth can measure temperature, registration identity information, the right side of the temporary added a bill, also used for registration. Young people dragging suitcases are the focus of the investigation, in addition to identity cards, but also need to show a train ticket to prove their city of origin. One of the village committee members who patrol here told our reporter, in addition, but also to call the landlord to pick up people, "if the landlord is not willing to assume responsibility, that they can not let them in. ". If the visitors and hubei-related, "directly hit 120 pull to go to the hospital, " but so far, no similar situation.

This print reporter walks to another gate, catch up with duty personnel's slack hour, after measured the body temperature, mixed in. Yang, the owner of the Menehua Hin supermarket, told this newspaper that he did not return to his hometown this year, guarding his supermarket and a dozen empty rooms. But the tenants have all returned home for the New Year. A few days ago, he called them one by one to tell the village committee, "don't go back to Beijing yet. ". Dongsanqi this area has many similar houses, rented to migrant workers, monthly rent in about 1,000(about 20 square meters kitchen and bathroom with a separate room) . Another landlord, surnamed Ye, told this newspaper that he managed hundreds of rooms, 70 or 80 of which were occupied by tenants who had returned home. At the request of the village committee, he had already passed on the notice of the suspension of his return to Beijing.

Yang told our reporter that he saw the situation is, January 30 morning or "not allowed" , to the evening "loose fast, put in some" , a few days ago, the number of migrant workers into the community is not much. Around 9:30, before our reporter left, he saw a young man hurrying with his suitcase on his way back to the south. He said he had just returned from Shandong and was blocked out. The Village Committee told him that he was "five minutes late. ". By what standard, he could not say, the precious five minutes had passed.

Quiet shot

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 31, the government of Beijing said that "except for essential industries, companies will start work on February 10" , delaying the impending return to Beijing by another week. However, the document still leaves room for companies to require employees to return to Beijing to work flexibly. Already back to Beijing office workers, many have been wandering outside for several days. One after another, tenants from seven other places in the north were turned away from rented residential areas. According to our reporter's incomplete statistics, most of these residential areas are managed by village committees. This type of residential area emphasizes "villagers' autonomy" , they think they have more freedom in the management of the community. They made requests to the tenants, "self-isolation outside 14 days" , "14 days after the production of three a hospital issued a health certificate.

On the same night that our reporter visited Dongsanqi village, "post-80s" Chai Meng and her family were several kilometers away at the gate of Dongerqi new village, rejected by the village committee. She told our reporter, they drove more than 1200 kilometers in a row, from Harbin back to Beijing, did not expect to return home in Beijing.

Here's Chai Meng's story.

"Beipiao" produced by new coronary pneumonia

On January 23, we set off from Beijing to my hometown of Harbin. I hesitated before I left. I followed the news of the epidemic every day, and I kept in mind the anti-pneumonia methods taught by academician Zhong Nanshan. So I figured I'd drive home, safer than planes and trains. My grandmother was not well and I had to go back to see her; the other reason I had to go back was my daughter, who was only four. Not long after the baby was born, I had to send her home to my mother for work. As a grandchild, as a daughter, as a mother, I need to go home.
On January 29th, we set off for Beijing again. The landlord had called earlier, asking for my and my family's identity information, and also asked where we were spending the new year, but did not say not to return. Our community is called Dongerqi new village, is a relocation community, we have rented here for two years, two-bedroom, rent 4,000 a month, the New Year just transferred to the landlord for three months 12,000 rent.
By the time we got to Dongerqixincun, it was 6:00 p.m. and it was already dark. Someone at the door took our temperature, checked us in, and told us we couldn't come in. Their exact words were, "quarantine yourself for 14 days, and then issue a health certificate from a top-three hospital, " so we could go in.
At first we tried to justify it to them, but could we at least go back and keep ourselves isolated. However, the district administrators spoke very hard and strongly disagreed, saying that they should be responsible for more than 1,000 villagers in the Dongerqi new village. "everyone is old above and small below. Please understand. " During the epidemic period, special policies are needed. In fact, I quite understand. But the irony is, we waited until almost 12:00 at the gate of our community, and we saw villagers coming and going, some without masks, some spitting everywhere, do you know where they drove, did they come back with the virus? If not, does this isolation make sense? And we return to Beijing from Harbin, why can not return to the community? Then I laughed and joked with my family, would the pneumonia virus identify people and target US outsiders?
Waiting at the gate of the community this evening, we met a total of three families in the same boat. One was a mother and her son from Tangshan, and I saw the mother holding the child in her arms, arguing, and turning away in anger; the other two, both returning from Inner Mongolia, both Married... with Children, and having failed in their negotiations, also left. We were the only ones left holding out hope for a few more hours.
We called 110, too. The man on the phone gave us the number of the local police station. The call went through, and the other side said there was nothing they could do. Until after 12:00, so we had to bail, and we spent the night at a B & B.
But the hotel said they closed after tonight, which means we'll be wandering around again tomorrow, having lived in Beijing for more than a decade and having to worry about where we'll be staying the next night. I've always liked the city of Beijing, where I went to college, worked, and had a family. In all my years, it was the first time I called the police. It was also the first time I felt like a stray dog. All Day and night, I was running around, worried about the epidemic of pneumonia, worried about my safety, also worried about my job, as well as the mortgage and car loan.
The front desk of the hotel near Dongsanqi told our reporter that they had stopped accepting guests (rebuttal still shot) 
The next morning, we returned to the Dongerqi new village, one is to try our luck, the other is to go back to get some supplies. I even told the village committee to cover me up or sterilize me, just let me in for a while and I'll be out soon. And they said to me, a minute in is the same as a day. They also stressed that the village could govern itself and that they were right to do so. Finally we had to give the landlord the key, let him go to the House to help out a few things.
Today, I saw a news report that the deputy director of the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Civil Affairs, said at a press conference that "no confirmed cases of pneumonia, no obvious fever or cough, should be allowed to enter the community freely. ". Encouraged by the news, we called the seven northern township governments and received a response that there had been no blanket eviction notices. Then we called the village committee of the Dongerqi new village and asked them if they could let us in.
They thought there was hope, but they stuck to their guns and said, "it [ the northern Qijia, Longhua County government ] will compromise, and we will not compromise. " . I'm worried now that if the outbreak continues, they won't let us back in 14 days.
After these two days of negotiation, I have a feeling that Dongerqi Xincun is protecting itself in a very confused way, believing that as long as we outsiders are expelled, they will be safe. But in fact, a little study of epidemic prevention and control knowledge, we can find that the autonomy of this community, few of the initiatives are truly scientific and effective. It was so cute, the first night, the guy who took our temperature, took my forehead temperature, and it was 34 degrees, 3, and I was so happy. In the simplest case of epidemic prevention and control, migrant workers return to Beijing and stay in hotels. Assuming one of these people is infected, doesn't that mean a greater risk. All the phone calls we could make, all the efforts we could make, and now we're waiting for the verdict.
Just now I saw a photo on Weibo of three boxes of materials donated to Wuhan. It was labeled "materials from Hubei Universities supported by the Hanyu Shuiping Kaoshi HSK affairs bureau" . It also had a line on it that read "Go China" , below there is a line of small print, "mountains and rivers, exotic, same day. ". These two words hit me suddenly, and they seemed to convey a beautiful emotion and complex emotions, so in the current situation of me, stupefied for a long time.
